focus.$description: Inner white boarder for primary focused button

full.$description: Use this border radius for pill shaped elements

Medium.$description: Default UI font. Most commonly used for body text.

Medium Bold.$description: Default UI font. Most commonly used for body text.

Small.$description: Small body text for discrete UI applications, such as helper, footnote text. Should be used sparingly across pages. Line-height matches Body (medium) at 20px.

Small Bold.$description: Small body text for discrete UI applications, such as helper, footnote text. Should be used sparingly across pages. Line-height matches Body (medium) at 20px.

Caption.$description: Compact small font with a smaller line height of 16px. Use it for single-line scenarios, as the small sizing doesnt pass accessibility requirements.

CodeBlock.$description: Default style for rendering code blocks.

Display.$description: Hero-style text for brand to product transition pages. Utilize Title (large) styles on narrow viewports.

Subtitle.$description: Page sections/sub headings, or less important object names in page titles (automated action titles, for example). Same line-height as title (medium).

Large.$description: Page headings for user-created objects, such as issues or pull requests. Use title (medium) styles on narrow viewports.

Medium.$description: Default page title. The 32px-equivalent line-height matches with button and other medium control heights. Great for page header composition.

Small.$description: Uses the same size as body (large) with a heavier weight of semibold (600).
